[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    172[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The code is pedagogically well-structured with excellent comments explaining the clinical reasoning behind each constraint. The protocol definitions, resource modeling, pharmacy coordination, and disruption handling sections are all strong. However, the core constraint formulation (Findings 1 and 2) contains fundamental errors in CP-SAT half-reification that would produce incorrect schedules. These aren't subtle edge cases; they're structural issues where the constraints are effectively unenforced. A reader implementing this pattern would get schedules with chair double-bookings and nursing capacity violations.
